The paper proposes a new data clustering method based on partitioning bipartite graphs, which is a common data structure in many data mining applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also focuses on document clustering, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves minimizing a normalized sum of edge weights, which is a common approach in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of assigning data objects to multiple clusters, which is a topic in both machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI, cs.AI).
